    article.main.list
        .exe
            section
                h1 MAYBE TYPE
                aside
                    time Published: 29 APR 2026
                +tex.
                    The $Maybe$ type (also called $Option$) is the disjoint union of the unit type $𝟏$ and a given type $A$.
                    It represents computations that may fail or return no value ($nothing$) or succeed with a value ($just$).
                +tex(true).
                    $$
                      Maybe(A) = 𝟏 + A
                    $$

            section
                h2 Formation
                +code.
                    def Maybe (A : U) : U := + 𝟏 A

                h2 Constructors
                +tex.
                    $Maybe$ has two constructors: $nothing$ (the failure case) and $just$ (the success case).
                +code.
                    def nothing (A : U) : Maybe A := inl 𝟏 A ★
                    def just (A : U) (a : A) : Maybe A := inr 𝟏 A a

                h2 Eliminators
                +tex.
                    The induction principle for $Maybe$ is derived from the induction principle of the disjoint union $+$.
                +code.
                    def maybe-ind (A : U) (P: Maybe A → U)
                        (n: P (nothing A)) (j: Π (x: A), P (just A x))
                      : Π (a: Maybe A), P a
                     := +-ind 𝟏 A P (ind₁ (λ (_ : 𝟏), P (nothing A)) n) j

                p.
                    Non-dependent versions:
                +code.
                    def maybe-rec (A P: U) (n: P) (j: A → P) : Maybe A → P
                     := maybe-ind A (λ (_ : Maybe A), P) n j

            section
                h2 Theorems
                +tex.
                    Standard computational rules follow from the corresponding rules of $+$.
                p.
                    (See $+$-β rules in the Either section for the computational behavior.)

